## Architecture

Before proceeding, let's adjust the architecture of our template project to match the MVVM pattern.

 **Step 1. Create folders named  *Models* ,  *Views* and  *ViewModels* :** 

 **In the Solution Explorer, right click the  *BarcodeScanner*  project, then** select  *Add... > New Folder* 


<img src="data:image/png;base64," style="undefined"/>


Name the newly created folder  *Views* :


<img src="data:image/png;base64," style="undefined"/>


Repeat this step two more times, naming the folders  *Models* and  *ViewModels.* 

After doing so, the Solution Explorer should look like this:


<img src="data:image/png;base64," style="undefined"/>


Â 

 **Step 2. Move  *MainPage.xaml* and  *MainPage.xaml.cs*  inside the  *Views* folder:** 


<img src="data:image/png;base64," style="undefined"/>


Â 

Step 3. Fix namespace referrences to match the solution:

Inside  *MainPage.xaml* , change the  *x:Class*  value to  *"BarcodeScanner.Views.MainPage"* 


<img src="data:image/png;base64," style="undefined"/>


Inside  *MainPage.xaml.cs* , change the namespace to  *BarcodeScanner.Views* 


<img src="data:image/png;base64," style="undefined"/>


Inside  *App.xaml.cs* , change the reference inside the constructor to  *BarcodeScanner.Views.MainPage();* 


<img src="data:image/png;base64," style="undefined"/>


Â 

After performing the steps above, the solution should look like this:
